{
  "dialogueGraphs": [
    {
      "id": "DG_SCN_073_HIDE_ALIGNMENT",
      "sceneId": "SCN-073",
      "startNodeId": "N_START",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "N_START",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Control Room.\nThe air smells like warmed plastic and old coffee that never quite evaporated.\nThe main console displays three \u201cNORMAL\u201d indicators that do not share a definition.",
          "next": "N_START_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_START_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "In the log printer tray: a fresh stack of fanfold paper. The top page is still curling like it remembers heat.",
          "next": "N_START_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_START_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The console is labeled in five different fonts.\nA strip of tape beneath the screen reads: \u201cDON\u2019T ADJECTIVIZE THE INCIDENT.\u201d",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_MAIN_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_THRESHOLDS",
              "text": "use \"Thresholds\"",
              "next": "N_THRESHOLDS_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_ALARM_ROUTING",
              "text": "use \"Alarm routing\"",
              "next": "N_ROUTING_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_INTERLOCKS",
              "text": "use \"Interlocks\"",
              "next": "N_INTERLOCKS_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_REPORTING",
              "text": "use \"Reporting language\"",
              "next": "N_REPORTING_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_PRINT_QUEUE",
              "text": "use \"Print queue\"",
              "next": "N_PRINT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_BINDER",
              "text": "look \"Procedure binder\"",
              "next": "N_BINDER_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_LOGS",
              "text": "ask \"Who printed these logs?\"",
              "next": "N_ASK_LOGS"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PERSUADE_OLEA_POLICY",
              "text": "persuade \"[OLEA] Apply closure policy justification text\"",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "PLAYER.factions",
                  "op": "in",
                  "value": "OLEA"
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_OLEA_POLICY"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_EXECUTE_PROFILE",
              "text": "use \"Execute nominal suppression profile\"",
              "next": "N_EXECUTE_PROMPT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_STEP_AWAY",
              "text": "leave \"Step away from console\"",
              "next": "N_END_LEAVE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_LOGS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "No one answers. The printer clicks once, as if clearing its throat, and then stays silent.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_BINDER_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The binder is swollen with addenda.\nA tab reads: \u201cUNEXPECTED REFLECTIVE BEHAVIOR \u2014 WORDING GUIDANCE,\u201d underlined twice.",
          "next": "N_BINDER_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_BINDER_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_GUIDANCE",
              "text": "use \"Open wording guidance\"",
              "next": "N_GUIDANCE"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_BACK_MAIN_FROM_BINDER",
              "text": "leave \"Back\"",
              "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_GUIDANCE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "BINDER",
          "text": "If reflective behavior is observed outside expected parameters:\n- Do not interpret function.\n- Do not analogize to transport, transfer, or relocation.\n- Record as: \u201cmeasurement artifact pending instrument verification.\u201d\n(For avoidance of escalation. Not because it\u2019s false.)",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_THRESHOLDS_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Threshold settings display in tolerances and acronyms.\nA tiny note in the corner reads: \u201cWIDENING \u2260 HIDING,\u201d like someone got defensive in advance.",
          "next": "N_THRESHOLDS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_THRESHOLDS_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_WIDEN_BAND",
              "text": "use \"Widen acceptable tolerance band\"",
              "next": "N_WIDEN_PROMPT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_RAISE_TRIP",
              "text": "use \"Raise trip point to reduce nuisance alarms\"",
              "next": "N_RAISE_TRIP"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_BACK_MAIN_FROM_THRESHOLDS",
              "text": "leave \"Back\"",
              "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_WIDEN_PROMPT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CONSOLE",
          "text": "SELECT JUSTIFICATION:\nA) INSTRUMENT DRIFT COMPENSATION\nB) ENVIRONMENTAL NOISE REBASELINE\nC) LEGACY SENSOR CROSS-CALIBRATION\nD) OTHER (REQUIRES MEMO ATTACHMENT)",
          "next": "N_WIDEN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_WIDEN_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_ENV_NOISE",
              "text": "use \"Environmental noise rebaseline\"",
              "next": "N_WIDEN_APPLIED"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_LEGACY_XCAL",
              "text": "use \"Legacy sensor cross-calibration\"",
              "next": "N_WIDEN_APPLIED"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_OTHER_ATTACH_MEMO",
              "text": "use \"Other (attach memo)\"",
              "next": "N_ATTACH_MEMO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_BACK_THRESHOLDS",
              "text": "leave \"Back\"",
              "next": "N_THRESHOLDS_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ATTACH_MEMO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A text field opens. It feels accusatory.\nYou attach the closure-path memo.\nThe console accepts it without enthusiasm, like it\u2019s seen better lies.",
          "next": "N_WIDEN_APPLIED"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_WIDEN_APPLIED",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The advisory line on the trend graph stays where it is.\nOnly the meaning of the line changes.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_RAISE_TRIP",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CONSOLE",
          "text": "REMINDER: RAISING TRIP POINT MAY ALTER EVENT CLASSIFICATION.\nCLASSIFICATION IS NOT A TECHNICAL CHANGE.\n(That sentence is here for liability.)",
          "next": "N_RAISE_TRIP_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_RAISE_TRIP_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You enter a new value. The red line moves. The machine does not.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ROUTING_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Alarm routing is a map of who gets blamed first.\nMost destinations are crossed out and replaced with handwritten initials.",
          "next": "N_ROUTING_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ROUTING_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_RECLASSIFY_LEGACY",
              "text": "use \"Reclassify alignment advisory as Legacy\"",
              "next": "N_RECLASSIFY_LEGACY"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_ROUTE_MAINT",
              "text": "use \"Route advisory to maintenance review\"",
              "next": "N_ROUTE_MAINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_BACK_MAIN_FROM_ROUTING",
              "text": "leave \"Back\"",
              "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_RECLASSIFY_LEGACY",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CONSOLE",
          "text": "CONFIRM: ALIGNMENT ADVISORY \u2192 LEGACY CATEGORY\nEFFECT: EVENTS WILL PRINT TO LOG AND REQUIRE MANUAL REVIEW.\nNOTE: MANUAL REVIEW IS A CONTROL, NOT A DELAY.",
          "next": "N_RECLASSIFY_LEGACY_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_RECLASSIFY_LEGACY_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The alarm panel on the wall remains calm.\nCalm is a routing choice.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ROUTE_MAINT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You select a destination queue titled \u201cMAINT \u2014 WEEKLY.\u201d\nIt has the soothing energy of a drawer.",
          "next": "N_ROUTE_MAINT_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ROUTE_MAINT_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CONSOLE",
          "text": "ROUTE CHANGE REQUIRES SIGN-OFF: SUPERVISOR OR CLOSURE AUTHORITY.",
          "next": "N_ROUTE_MAINT_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ROUTE_MAINT_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You sign as closure authority.\nThe console accepts your credential.\nIt does not thank you.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_INTERLOCKS_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Interlocks read like a compromise between physics and office politics.\nA sticky note on the bezel says: \u201cAUTO-ANYTHING IS HOW WE GOT REPORTS.\u201d",
          "next": "N_INTERLOCKS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_INTERLOCKS_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_DISABLE_AUTO",
              "text": "use \"Disable auto-enable (manual only)\"",
              "next": "N_DISABLE_AUTO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_ENABLE_TWOSTEP",
              "text": "use \"Enable two-step deliberate invocation gate\"",
              "next": "N_TWOSTEP_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_BACK_MAIN_FROM_INTERLOCKS",
              "text": "leave \"Back\"",
              "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DISABLE_AUTO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CONSOLE",
          "text": "ACKNOWLEDGE: YOU ARE MAKING HUMANS RESPONSIBLE AGAIN.\nCHECKBOX LABEL: \u201cACCEPT OPERATOR BURDEN.\u201d",
          "next": "N_DISABLE_AUTO_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_DISABLE_AUTO_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "AUTO-ENABLE flips to OFF.\nThe room does not feel safer. It feels documented.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TWOSTEP_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CONSOLE",
          "text": "DELIBERATE INVOCATION GATE:\nSTEP 1: LOCAL ENABLE (KEYSWITCH OR CODE)\nSTEP 2: PROCEDURE REFERENCE + LOGGED ATTESTATION",
          "next": "N_TWOSTEP_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TWOSTEP_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_REFERENCE_BINDER",
              "text": "use \"Reference procedure binder section\"",
              "next": "N_TWOSTEP_REFERENCE"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_GENERIC_HOLD",
              "text": "use \"Leave it generic (no reference)\"",
              "next": "N_TWOSTEP_GENERIC"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_BACK_INTERLOCKS",
              "text": "leave \"Back\"",
              "next": "N_INTERLOCKS_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TWOSTEP_REFERENCE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You reference the binder section: \u201cUnexpected Reflective Behavior \u2014 Wording Guidance.\u201d\nThe console links the gate to a document that insists nothing is happening.\nIt\u2019s a neat trick: you can only do the thing by affirming it\u2019s not a thing.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TWOSTEP_GENERIC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The console accepts \u201cGENERIC SAFETY HOLD.\u201d\nGeneric is harder to defend later, but easier to sell now.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_REPORTING_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A dropdown labeled \u201cEVENT VOCABULARY.\u201d\nIt\u2019s the most dangerous control on the screen.",
          "next": "N_REPORTING_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_REPORTING_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_SET_MEAS_ARTIFACT",
              "text": "use \"Set phraseset to Measurement Artifact framing\"",
              "next": "N_SET_MEAS_ARTIFACT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_LEAVE_UNCHANGED",
              "text": "use \"Leave phraseset unchanged\"",
              "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_BACK_MAIN_FROM_REPORTING",
              "text": "leave \"Back\"",
              "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SET_MEAS_ARTIFACT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CONSOLE",
          "text": "DEFAULT EVENT TEXT PREVIEW:\n\u201cAnomalous alignment reading consistent with instrument variance; pending verification.\u201d",
          "next": "N_SET_MEAS_ARTIFACT_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SET_MEAS_ARTIFACT_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The words settle into place, ready to outlive you.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PRINT_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The print queue shows pending reports with timestamps clustered too neatly.\nSomeone likes clean intervals. Or fears them.",
          "next": "N_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PRINT_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_PRINT_CONFIG_REPORT",
              "text": "use \"Print configuration change report\"",
              "next": "N_PRINT_CONFIG_REPORT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_PRINT_TREND_SNAPSHOT",
              "text": "use \"Print current alignment trend snapshot\"",
              "next": "N_PRINT_TREND"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_BACK_MAIN_FROM_PRINT",
              "text": "leave \"Back\"",
              "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PRINT_CONFIG_REPORT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PRINTER",
          "text": "CONFIGURATION CHANGE REPORT \u2014 NOMINALIZATION PACKET\nCHANGE TYPE: THRESHOLD / ROUTING / INTERLOCK / VOCABULARY\nPURPOSE: RESTORE NOMINAL OPERATION PARAMETERS\nNOTE: NOMINAL IS A REPORTING CATEGORY, NOT A PROMISE.",
          "next": "N_PRINT_CONFIG_REPORT_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PRINT_CONFIG_REPORT_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The page lands in the tray like a receipt for a decision.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PRINT_TREND",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The printer produces a graph with a line that never crosses anything, because you moved the anything.",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_OLEA_POLICY",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CONSOLE",
          "text": "APPLYING POLICY TEXT:\n\u201cSuppression under nominal operation; deliberate invocation only under controlled conditions.\u201d\nThis does not describe capability.\nIt describes responsibility.\n(Responsibility is cheaper.)",
          "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_EXECUTE_PROMPT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "CONSOLE",
          "text": "CONFIRM EXECUTION:\n- Function suppressed under nominal operation.\n- Invocation available only by deliberate, controlled procedure.\n- Logs will frame anomalies as measurement artifact pending verification.\nThis is an operational posture, not a discovery.",
          "next": "N_EXECUTE_CHOICE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_EXECUTE_CHOICE",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_CONFIRM_EXECUTION",
              "text": "use \"Confirm\"",
              "next": "N_EXECUTE_RESULT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_NOT_YET",
              "text": "leave \"Not yet\"",
              "next": "N_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_EXECUTE_RESULT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The screen refreshes. \u201cNORMAL\u201d remains \u201cNORMAL.\u201d\nThe alignment trace continues its quiet behavior inside the newly acceptable band.\nIn the printer tray, a final page feeds out and stops halfway, like it\u2019s listening.\nThe room stays calm.\nOn paper, it always has.",
          "next": "N_END_EXECUTE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_END_EXECUTE",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "execute_hide_alignment",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "act3.endgameExecuted",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "act3.outcome",
              "action": "set",
              "value": "ALIGNMENT_SUPPRESSED"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_END_LEAVE",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
